
Prospect Hill, 5 December 1775. Informs GW that Private Ralph Morgan of his regiment hath a Wife and two Children destitute of an House to cover them, & his Household Furniture in the Streets. Morgan wants an eight-day furlough, But, as that Regard which the Colo. is happy in paying to General Orders will not admit of a regimental Relief (Morgan declining the Service), begs his Excellencys Commiseration for the Poor Man.1
